{
    "Body": " Chief Information Officer (CIO) Pivotal Technology Professionals - United States Apply Now Job Details Full-time | Part-time | ContractEstimated: $110,000 - $150,000 a year Qualifications Project Management ITIL IT Service Management Program Management AI Master's Degree Bachelor's Degree Full Job Description Duration Part-time or full-time based on client engagement Location Locations throughout the United States and/or virtual remote locations Compensation Commensurate with experience, certification, and education Summary Pivotal Technology Professionals is currently hiring Chief Information Officers, Chief Technology Officers, and Technology Directors to provide virtual, part-time, and interim technology leadership services to our clients. Client engagements will be a combination of on-site work, virtual remote work, and a hybrid combining both on-site and virtual remote work. The travel requirements will be established before the start of the engagement. This is a part-time or contract position. Compensation is based on experience, certification, and education. Duties: Each client engagement is unique. The high-level requirements for the engagement will be determined before the client engagement starts. However, the specific client goals must be initially clarified and understood at the start of the engagement. These duties may include the following: Understand the client\u2019s specific goals that they want to achieve from the engagement. Document the goals and scope of the engagement, review with the client to ensure accuracy. Provide a time estimate to complete the engagement. Align the overall IT strategy with business requirements. Identify the technology services required to support the client\u2019s customers, partners, suppliers, and internal business operations. Analyze the technology services that are required to support the client\u2019s business. Perform an assessment of current services. Document the results of the assessment including suggestions for new technology services, updates to existing services, and termination of existing services. Document recommendations to the client based on the outcome of the assessment. Review the IT organization structure, resources, and skills and make change recommendations based on review. Lead initiatives to plan, design, build, deploy, monitor, and improve the technology services that are required to support the client\u2019s business. Provide advice, research, recommendations, and guidance for incorporating one or more specific technology product and service offerings into the organization. This includes the high-level approach, required resources, budget, and duration to integrate. Some of these emerging technology trends may include: \u2013 Artificial Intelligence, Machine Learning, Deep Learning, Ethics, and Bias \u2013 Digital Transformation and Services \u2013 Internet of Things (IoT) \u2013 Mobile Technology \u2013 Predictive Analytics, Data Science, and Big Data \u2013 Cloud Migration, Multi-cloud, and On-Premises Enterprise \u2013 Network Modernization, SDN, SD-WAN, and Edge Computing \u2013 Cyber Security, Privacy, Data Protection, and Regulatory Compliance \u2013 Blockchain \u2013 Communications, Collaboration, and the Future of Work \u2013 Agile Methods, DevOps, and Cloud-Native Design \u2013 Employee Engagement, Experience, and Retention Prepare for and conduct review meetings with the client\u2019s leadership executives that include engagement scope, strategy, service performance, engagement deliverables, and progress updates. Create engagement deliverables including: \u2013 Business objectives and scope document \u2013 Action plans including approach, budget and duration \u2013 Technology service assessment and recommendations documentation \u2013 Technology service inventory, requirements and design documentation \u2013 Presentations to client business leaders Qualifications: \u2013 Bachelor\u2019s or Master\u2019s degree in computer science, information systems, or equivalent. Advanced degree preferred. \u2013 At least 15 years of experience participating in technology initiatives with a minimum of 5 years in a senior technology leadership role. \u2013 Experience working with ITSM (IT Service Management), ITIL (IT Infrastructure Library), TOGAF (The Open Group Architecture Framework), COBIT (Control Objectives for Information and Related Technologies) (Governance), KT (Kepner-Tregoe) are a plus. \u2013 Experience leading a PMO (Program Management Office) and formal project management a plus. \u2013 Sophisticated interpersonal skills including excellent written & oral communications, and presentation skills. \u2013 Must be authorized to work in the United States without sponsorship Notices: Principals only. Recruiters, please do not contact us for this position do NOT contact us with unsolicited services or offers Qualified and interested candidates, kindly email your resume to: applicant@pivotaltechpros.com ", 
